15#ifndef ISC_STDTIME_H
16#define ISC_STDTIME_H 1
17
18/*! \file */
19
20#include <isc/lang.h>
21#include <inttypes.h>
22
23/*%
24 * It's public information that 'isc_stdtime_t' is an unsigned integral type.
25 * Applications that want maximum portability should not assume anything
26 * about its size.
27 */
28typedef uint32_t isc_stdtime_t;
29
30ISC_LANG_BEGINDECLS
31/* */
32void
33isc_stdtime_get(isc_stdtime_t *t);
34/*%<
35 * Set 't' to the number of seconds since 00:00:00 UTC, January 1, 1970.
36 *
37 * Requires:
38 *
39 *\li 't' is a valid pointer.
40 */
41
42#define isc_stdtime_convert32(t, t32p) (*(t32p) = t)
43/*
44 * Convert the standard time to its 32-bit version.
45 */
46
47ISC_LANG_ENDDECLS
48
49#endif /* ISC_STDTIME_H */
